Solutions were given out to each of these challenges faced by the farmers. There were demonstrations on which Fungicide to apply and the right quantity to use. Other Cultural and chemical control methods were also taught. NA NA

Sierra Leone BAFS Training/Capacity Building/Workshop Cocoa Cashew Coffee The topics discussed during the training session have enhanced participants to be gainfully aware of the opportunity and challenges to promote the quality management practices and marketing of the cocoa, coffee and cashew economy. The time allocated to the training was not enough despite the set of topics for the training were discussed. The training session should cater for an extra day for site visit to experience on site practical exercises to help participants to relate with the theoretical aspects of the topics discussed.
Sierra Leone BAFS Training/Capacity Building/Workshop Cashew The training is essential as it provides the basis for capacity building and outline the structures of the FSCs and the role of members in the functionality of the FSCs scheme. The timing of the training was not appropriate for a few farmers as they were engaged in their upland rice cultivation, however the participants were able to block time to attend the training. Engagement with farmers to state the timeline of the training to ensure adequate participation of farmers.
Sierra Leone BAFS Training/Capacity Building/Workshop Cashew Coffee Cocoa The training has outlined the concept and functional activities of the FSCs to its beneficiaries. Many farmers find it difficult in accessing markets to purchase their farm tools, inputs, tools and services but the bases of this training have heralded the exposition of farmers to tackle the bottleneck in accessing inputs and services by linkage to the farmers support centers. The majority of the participants were late for the training despite being a community-based training and as such the training was delayed to start on time. The training should be done twice a year depending on the availability of funds especially during the planting season for inputs support.
Sierra Leone BAFS Training/Capacity Building/Workshop Cocoa Cashew Coffee The output of the training on the farmer support centre has impacted the knowledge and awareness of farmers on the operation of the farmer's support centre and the services it can offer to enhance sustainable production in their farming activities. Mobilisation of participants to attend the training was a bit challenging despite it being community-based training. Follow-up training should be done subsequently during the planting season thus leveraging the support of the FSCs for immediate inputs and services for farmers.
Sierra Leone BAFS Training/Capacity Building/Workshop Cocoa Cashew Coffee The training was essential as because it is a capacity-building platform and it has helped farmers to be abreast of the functions of the FSCs in providing inputs supplies and services to maximise production. The period stated for the training was a bit challenging because few farmers were not present at the time of the training due to the activities of the upland rice cultivation. Engagement with farmers to state their convenient time within the stipulated implementation period of the project for maximum participation.
